    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe statusline item `%=`, which should create the \"separation point between alignment sections\" doesn't work inside a fixed-width item group.\n\nThis is a regression when used in `rulerformat` and the ruler is shown in the statusline.\nThe ruler does not have this issue when shown in the cmdline.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nMinimal `.vimrc` to reproduce that works in both Neovim and vim:\n```vim\nset ruler\nset laststatus=2\nset rulerformat=%20(%l,%c%V%=%P%m%)\n```\n\nThe problem only appears\n- in the statusline (`laststatus=2`), but not in the cmdline (`laststatus=1`)\n- if `%=` is inside a fixed-width item group, e.g. `%20(...%)`\n\nNB: the default rulerformat `%-14.(%l,%c%V%) %P` (or rather the fall-back in the default statusline) does not have this issue because the left-alignment is not created with `%=`, but I use it to ensure a fixed length of the whole ruler since `%m` has variable length.\n\nInterestingly, the statusline itself does not seem to have fully supported `%=` even before 0.12, not even in vim. I.e. the following `.vimrc` shows the same error both in vim and Neovim (0.11 or 0.12):\n```vim\nset laststatus=2\nset statusline=%20(%l,%c%V%=%P%m%)\n```\nIt would of course be nice to support this in the statusline directly too, as advertised in `:help statusline`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe left part (line, column, virtual column) should be left-aligned, while the right part (percentage through file and modified flag) should be right-aligned. Instead, there is no space in between.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2 (cannot reproduce with 0.11.7)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nbehaves the same in statusline, behaves differently in rulerformat inside statusline, vim 9.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 25.11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty or tty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty or linux\n\n### Installation\n\nnix with channel https://nixos.org/channels/nixpkgs-unstable",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I'd like to create a PR myself, but I have a further suggestion.\nCurrently, truncation markers `%<` are allowed in item groups, but they are processed at the end.\nI'd like to scope them to the item group they are contained in. This would be a breaking change, but I couldn't come up with a good reason for the current behaviour.\n\nExample use case: truncating the git branch from the right, but the file name from the left as usual, e.g.\n```vim\nset stl=%.10(branch:\\ %{%system('echo\\ -n\\ $(git\\ branch\\ --show-current\\ 2>/dev/null)')%}%<%)\\ %<%f\n```\n\nI'll gladly create a separate issue for this if required.",
