            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I could only come up with contrived examples. And it's broken anyway. In the following example, the surrounding item group is hidden, but the `%<`'s position is not adjusted accordingly, so that the file path is truncated 6 cells in:\n```vim\nset stl=%(hidden%<%)%f\n```\nI find it hard to believe that anyone would _really_ [rely on this](https://xkcd.com/1172/)...",
