            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Let's assume my terminal is 50 columns wide and the following example:\n```sh\nnvim --clean /usr/local/very/long/file_path/that/will/need/to/be/truncated +\"set stl=%(hidden%<%)%f\"\n```\nCurrently, this yields:\n```\n/usr/l<ng/file_path/that/will/need/to/be/truncated\n```\nAfter scoping the `%<` to its item group, it will be ignored and the default top-level truncation from the left kicks in:\n```\n<ery/long/file_path/that/will/need/to/be/truncated\n```",
